K - The type of keys in the BST, which must be comparable.
V - The type of values stored in the BST.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Benchmark<K[]>
public class BSTBenchmark<K extends Comparable<K>,V> extends Benchmark_Timer<K[]>
A class that benchmarks Binary Search Tree (BST) operations using various configurations, including experiments with different tree structures, input sizes, and operational modes. This class extends the Benchmark_Timer to provide timing-based benchmarking functionality.

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      The main method serves as the entry point to the program. It logs the benchmarking process and takes command-line arguments that represent integers. Each integer is passed to the doBenchmark method for executing a binary search tree (BST) benchmarking test.
      Parameters:
      args - an array of strings representing command-line arguments. Each argument is expected to be an integer, which determines the number of words used in benchmarking and the associated resources to be loaded.

    • runBenchmark

      public double runBenchmark(Supplier<K[]> supplier)
      Executes a benchmarking process using the provided supplier and the number of defined runs. This method utilizes the supplier to generate input data, and benchmarks the performance by invoking the runFromSupplier method.
      Parameters:
      supplier - a supplier that provides an array of elements of type K. These elements serve as the input data for the benchmark.
      Returns:
      the average time in milliseconds for each run during the benchmarking process.
